  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Imaging of the ischaemic penumbra with a particular diffusion-weighted imaging (DWI)/
      perfusion-weighted imaging (PWI) mismatch is a promising approach to the selection of
      patients with acute ischaemic stroke for trials of intervention. The investigators want to
      apply multimodal resonance imaging methods such as functional magnetic resonance imaging (
      fMRI), diffusion tensor imaging (DTI), arterial spin labeling (ASL) to guide treatment and
      predict the prognosis of stroke.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
